## 9. FILES TO IGNORE — DO NOT PORT

These are Replit-only patterns that violate the Next.js App Router architecture:

| Pattern | Replit Source | Reason |
|---------|--------------|--------|
| `wouter` `<Link>` | Most pages | Use `next/link` |
| `useSeoMeta()` hook | All pages | Use `generateMetadata()` |
| `useToast()` | All managers | Use `sonner` `toast.success/error` |
| `@workspace/api-client-react` | All hooks | Use module services with `apiAxios` |
| `@workspace/db` | All routes | Frontend imports from `@/src/lib/types`, backend from `@/db/schema` |
| `@workspace/api-zod` | All routes | Use `lib/validators/` (frontend) and module `validator.ts` (backend) |
| Vite config (`vite.config.ts`) | Frontend | Not applicable |
| `index.html` + `main.tsx` | Frontend | Replaced by Next.js App Router |
| `react-router-dom`/`wouter` | Frontend | Replaced by Next.js routing |
| `express-session` | Backend `adminAuth.ts` | We use JWT (access + refresh) |
| `ObjectStorageService` (Replit GCS) | Backend | Replace with AWS S3 in B6 |
| `useImageUpload` from `@/hooks/use-image-upload` | Frontend | Rewrite as `use-s3-upload.ts` in F11 |
| Components without `"use client"` directive | All admin | Must add `"use client"` since they have state/handlers |

